com.sonf.core.filter

接口 IFilter

  • 所有已知实现类:
    IFilterAdapter, ProtocolFilter

    public interface IFilter
    A filter which intercepts IOHandler events to do something like transforming message or performing measurement , etc. A filter instance should be register to the controller's FilterChainBuilder, and it will be added to session's IFilterChain, so event on this session will pass by the filters on the chain one by one. Note that the event which is fired from the controller to outside will pass the chain from Head to Tail and finally to the IOHandler. On the contrary the event fired from outside to the controller will pass the chain form Tail o Head. This is important if you use the filter chain to do message encode/decode or wrap/unwrap. Don't make a wrong order when adding your filters into the chain.

        void onPreAdd(IFilterChain parent,
              java.lang.String name)
       throws java.lang.Exception
        Invoked before this filter is added to the specified parent. Please note that this method can be invoked more than once if this filter is added to more than one parents.
        参数:
        parent - the parent who called this method
        name - the name assigned to this filter
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - If an error occurred while processing the event
